# Ensure the necessary dependencies are loaded
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

# Create the dataframe for the heat map
heat = pd.read_csv(url)

# Create a function that will generae a correlation heat map for any dataset
def correlation_heatmap(heat):
    correlations = heat.corr()

    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(15,15))
    sns.heatmap(correlations, vmax=1.0, center=0, fmt='.2f',
                square=True, linewidths=.5, annot=True, cbar_kws={"shrink": .70})
    plt.show();

# Call the function passing the dataframe as the parameter
correlation_heatmap(heat)

heat = pd.read_csv(url)

def correlation_heatmap(heat):
    correlations = heat.corr()

    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(20,20))
    sns.heatmap(correlations, vmax=1.0, center=0, fmt='.2f',
                square=True, linewidths=.5, annot=True, cbar_kws={"shrink": .70})
    plt.show();
